x4freetext: Main Reference
Fusion Neutronics Source Facility
Well-type high-purity germanium detector
Effective incident neutron energy at the irradiation
position was determined by the ratio of 90Zr(n,2n)89Zr
and 93Nb(n,2n)92m-Nb reaction rates
Corrections were made for time fluctuation of neutron
flux, for contribution of low energy neutrons below
10 MeV, thickness of samples, self-absorption and
sum-peak effect of gamma-rays
Total error equal to quadratic sum of -
Experimental Measurements Error, and
Errors of Nuclear Data.
